args: What's wrong with this person?\nHe smells awful!
Those children are ALIVE.\nYou cannot eat them YET.
If you're still HUNGRY, then go raid a gug's\nGRAVE. Otherwise...
Looks like he's given up on you TWO.\nAre you girls OKAY?
You mean the monster Akasha told us\nabout?! You're not gonna eat us, are you?!
No, NO. We only eat the DEAD.\nIt's very rare to see one stray and\nattack the LIVING.
More importantly, it seems you two are\nLOST. I can tell, because we were the\nSAME.
My whole squad accidentally wandered\ninto this WORLD. After living here for so\nlong, we eventually became GHOULS.
We look human now, but before long, we'll\nprobably start looking more like DOGS.\nHeeHEEheeHEEhee!
So if we get stuck here, we're gonna\nturn into monsters too?!
Not NECESSARILY. But I do know it's\nnot good for kids to be in this WORLD.\nHow about I take you back to your OWN?
You mean you know how to get back?
We ghouls like to steal corpses from the\nwaking world as WELL, so we know a\nsecret way to get in and out of HERE.

Oh, you don't need to be suspicious of ME.
I'm doing this out of the kindness of my
HEART. I'm just so glad to talk to another
person after so LONG.
What do you wanna do, Lathna?
We followed Richard. Though he looked scary,\nhe was cheerful and kind to us.
He informed us that we had indeed\nwandered into the Dreamlands.
In this WORLD, cats are WARRIORS.\nThey're intelligent and fiercely LOYAL.
The cat that rescued you two might have\nbeen one you took care of at some POINT.
That black kitty... It might have been the\none who befriended me back in Kyril.

Those rats are pretty troublesome, but it's
possible to communicate with them if you
know their LANGUAGE. That makes them
one of the less awful denizens HERE.

For instance, there are invisible
caterpillars that lurk in the ravine up
AHEAD. They devour anything unlucky
enough to fall into their DOMAIN.
But more terrifying still are those\nwho guard the Great ONES.

In the epic poem GRASTAEA, as well as
the Tome of CREATION, there are countless
tales of these abnormal beings known as
the Great ONES.

Guarding them is a ruler and an
OVERSEER. Though they work together
in this SENSE, they are also in direct
opposition with each OTHER.

If you were to get mixed up in their
BATTLE, it would be OVER. It is told that
those who do go mad with FEAR and lose
all sense of SELF.
What do we do if we ever run into them?
Good QUESTION... I would say you'd need\nan emotional pillar of strength to maintain\nyour SANITY.
If you have happy memories you can turn\nTO, you should be able to stay sane no\nmatter what terror you may FACE.
Eeek!\nS-something's coming down from the sky!
Oh, no need to WORRY.\nThat is a simple NIGHTGAUNT.
It only looks SCARY. They won't hurt you\nas long as you stay out of their TERRITORY.
EEEK! Then why is it grabbing me?!
Is this one of its friends?! Aaaah!
Why would a nightgaunt go after someone\noutside of its TERRITORY? No... Could it\nbe HIM?!
Let go of me! LET GO OF ME!
(Where is this thing trying to take me?)
The ground's getting closer and closer...!
What's that? Oh... A deer.\nYou really scared me, you kno
The ground swallowed it! No, that's not it...\nThere's something IN the ground here!
It's trying to pull me in too!\nAAAAAHHHHH!
Ngh... Where did that monster take me?
It looks like a big mansion, but it's so\ncreepy... *sob* I'm so scared... Eek!
I tripped... I've gotta get all my things\nback in my pouch... *sob* *hic*
Oh. This is the matching scrunchie\nfor the one I gave Lathna...
Come on, Pia. You're not the only one\nwho's scared right now. Lathna must be\njust as terrified.
If she saw me like this,\nit'd only make her feel worse.
So this is the dreamer the overseer\nbrought.
I am told the humans have named me...\nthe Lord of the Great Abyss.
Um... Are you the one who sent those\nmonsters to bring me here?
Indeed. The nightgaunts are my servants.
What happened to my friend, Lathna?
Your friend? Ha ha ha...\nHA HA HA HA!
Now this is most amusing. I never thought\nI'd see the day when someone would call\nhim friend!

I had the nightgaunts drop him into the
Demon's Pit. I imagine the caterpillars
have long since dragged him into the
ground and begun their fetid feast.
Lathna's been eaten?! No! It can't be!
I suspect my longstanding foe is far too\nresilient to die such an inglorious death.

O turgid maggots, with your pitiful lust
for flesh. For the witless sin of swallowing
We of a thousand forms, We devour you
from within.

We are the key. The Emissary of the
Ancient One. The scent of entrails is a
most disagreeable gambol. We shall
retaliate for this plot hidden in the abyss.
